      "code": "{\"command\": \"python \\\"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\Documents\\\\netflix_quality_processor.py\\\" \\\"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\Downloads\\\\Anna_Karaoke_Lyrics_Video.mp4\\\"\", \"description\": \"Process video with Netflix quality standards\", \"timeout\": 600000}",
      "output": "\r\n============================================================\r\nNETFLIX QUALITY PROCESSOR\r\n============================================================\r\nInput: Anna_Karaoke_Lyrics_Video.mp4\r\n============================================================\r\n\r\n[1/5] Extracting audio...\r\n[2/5] Normalizing audio (Netflix -27 LKFS)...\r\n  Normalizing audio to Netflix spec (-27 LKFS)...\r\n  Measuring loudness (EBU R128)...\r\n    Measured: -14.8 LUFS, TP: -0.3 dBTP\r\n  Measuring loudness (EBU R128)...\r\n    Final: -27.0 LUFS, TP: -12.5 dBTP\r\n[3/5] Extracting video...\r\n[4/5] Encoding video (H.265 CRF 20)...\r\n  Encoding video (CRF 20, slow, libx265)...\r\n    Saved: C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\Netflix_Quality_Output\\temp\\Anna_Karaoke_Lyrics_Video_video_encoded.mp4\r\n[5/5] Combining audio + video...\r\n\r\n============================================================\r\nPROCESSING COMPLETE\r\n============================================================\r\nOutput: C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\Netflix_Quality_Output\\Anna_Karaoke_Lyrics_Video_NETFLIX_QUALITY.mp4\r\n\r\nNetflix Specifications Applied:\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\netflix_quality_processor.py\", line 441, in <module>\r\n    main()\r\n  File \"C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\netflix_quality_processor.py\", line 432, in main\r\n    processor.process_karaoke_video(input_file)\r\n  File \"C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\netflix_quality_processor.py\", line 333, in process_karaoke_video\r\n    print(f\"  Audio: -27 LKFS (�2 LU), True Peak \\u2264 -2 dBTP\")\r\n  File \"C:\\Python312\\Lib\\encodings\\cp1252.py\", line 19, in encode\r\n    return codecs.charmap_encode(input,self.errors,encoding_table)[0]\r\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\nUnicodeEncodeError: 'charmap' codec can't encode character '\\u2264' in position 37: character maps to <undefined>\r\n",
