    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "A **playback catalogue** means creating a **professional, standardized library** of karaoke videos that are all:\n\n1. **Consistent** - Same loudness, same quality, same format\n2. **Performance-ready** - Optimized for live speakers\n3. **Organized** - Easy to find and play any song\n4. **Professional-grade** - Netflix broadcast standards\n\n---\n\n### **What \"Professionalisation\" Involves:**\n\n| Aspect | What It Means | Netflix Standard |\n|--------|---------------|------------------|\n| **Loudness** | All songs same volume | -27 LKFS |\n| **Peak Levels** | No clipping on speakers | -2 dBTP max |\n| **Video Quality** | Consistent, clear lyrics | H.265 CRF 20 |\n| **Format** | Universal playback | MP4 + AAC audio |\n| **Metadata** | Title, artist, key | Embedded tags |\n\n---\n\n### **Why This Matters for Live Performance:**\n\n- **No volume jumps** between songs\n- **Lyrics always readable** on screen\n- **Audio never distorts** on Bluetooth/speakers\n- **Quick transitions** between tracks\n- **Backup copies** at highest quality\n\n---\n\n### **Want Me to Build This System?**\n\nI can create:\n1. **Batch processor** - Process 100+ videos to same spec\n2. **Catalogue database** - Track all songs, keys, tempos\n3. **Quality validator** - Check every video meets Netflix spec\n4. **Export tool** - Create USB/drive ready for any device\n\n**Is Anna building a karaoke business or performance act?** This helps me understand what level of professionalisation she needs.",
